Oct 23 2005	Stay away and watch yourself	Just returned from Montreal, stayed in Champ-de-Mar. The location of the hotel is good, a few steps from Old Montreal. The second good thing is breakfast. All the other things are terrible. The rooms are small (that's OK) and extremely smelly with the strong smell of cheap odorizer. Air condition was hardly felt. And you can't open the window!!! The window is closed forever. I was unable to stay in the room more then 20 minutes. On reception I was told that windows are closed for security reasons. It was impossible to cancel the reservation because of cancellation fee of 100%. Interestingly, for additional 70$ I was given a room with a small window amenable to opening (probably the security situation in this room was different).Stay away and watch yourself	
